parameters:
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] It seems your soldiers can't get up. Most of them couldn't even scratch the
steel soldiers and fled, it seems.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] The essence of Blue sorcery is learning magic and acquiring techniques.
Therefore, no matter how high-ranking a sorcerer is, they cannot fully
comprehend a magic they see for the first time.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Becky, it's okay. Sorry I'm late.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Don't call me by my name so casually, mad princess Lucia. You should be
ashamed.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Luna, it seems you've finally mastered Blue magic. Wonderful.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Born into a family that has passed down Blue magic for generations, you were
particularly skilled in Blue magic even among your kin.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] The essence of my Blue sorcery is learning magic. No matter how excellent a
sorcerer is, they cannot defend against the rare magics obtained from all over
the world.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] The difference between an Blue sorcerer and an ordinary sorcerer is that they
make any magic they see once their own.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Moreover, Luna, you enhance the Blue magic you learn once by adding your
original magic to it.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Black witch... Lucia, I will definitely defeat you.

Sylvia: I can't imagine Lucia losing, but Blue magic itself is a threatening
existence.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] There is no technique I cannot learn. Lucia, I will learn all of your attack
magic.

[Steel Soldier] Hey you, what are you blabbering about? I'll make you suffer the
same fate as your comrades.
[Steel Soldier] Like you could ever match Lady Lucia. I'll twist and kill you.
[Steel Soldier] Take this! My prideful headbutt! Here it comes!

[Steel Soldier] Gah... You learned and copied my headbutt... And it's even more
powerful than mine...
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Now do you understand? The techniques I can learn are not limited to magic.

[Steel Soldier] Damn... A sorcerer who learns the opponent's techniques? You've
got to be kidding...
[Steel Soldier] My body is melting...! What is this...!?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Yes, this is one of the secret techniques of my blue magic, "Acid Rain." It's
an original spell of mine that only rains acid on the enemy.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Amazing...! As expected of Luna. She took down all the steel soldiers in an
instant.

Sylvia: As I thought, she's not to be underestimated. The blue sorceress Luna...
she's beyond imagination.
Sylvia: With this match, even Lucia might not be certain of victory.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] A defensive barrier, huh? It seems it's not just an ordinary shell.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] It's futile. I instantly covered my body with a magic barrier that neutralizes
acid.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Luna, surely you didn't think you could defeat me with just that, did you?
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Now, what will you show me next?
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] I thought I couldn't defeat you without using my secret magic.
Sylvia: Luna's existence is too dangerous.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Lucia, let me ask you one last thing before the end.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] It's rumored that you killed your own mother to inherit the direct line of
sorcery. Is that true? Lady Leysia, your mother, was kind to me.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] It's true. I killed my own mother. I killed Leysia. What of it?
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] There's nothing more to discuss with you.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] I will erase you with my blue magic.
Sylvia: Lucia! Now's your chance to kill Luna!
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Damn it... I forgot there was another one.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] That is... Sylvia of the magical kingdom of Valentia... ugh

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Sylvia? Why is a general from Valentia in the imperial capital of
Jupiterino...?
Sylvia: Lucia! Kill Luna! If you leave her be, she will surely become a threat!
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] However, what Sylvia says makes sense.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] If I leave you as you are, you will certainly become a threat to me. It's best
to nip dangerous buds in the bud.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] It's a shame to kill such a genius though.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] However, I am a fair mage.
\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Sorry to Sylvia, but since you interfered in this duel, I won't take your life.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] However... indeed, you are too dangerous a being for me. There's no doubt that
you are a threat to me.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] I won't take your life. However, I will seal your magic power. Your sorcery
will be sealed.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Luna, I will make it so you can never use magic again. That way, you might as
well be dead.

\C[17][Lucia]\C[0] Yes. That way, you'll be like a waterfowl that's had its wings plucked. From
now on, you won't be able to oppose me anymore.

And so, Luna had her magic power taken away by Lucia and became unable to use
any magic at all.

Luna and Becky returned to their village, but they were met with harsh
reprimands and cold treatment from the village elders.

As a show of force, Lucia decided to impose triple the taxes on the village of
Sheena where Luna and the others lived.
She also punished those who joined the rebellion with whipping.

Luna and her childhood friend Noah, as well as Becky's husband Pole, became
paralyzed from the waist down after the battle with the steel soldiers,
conscious but unable to move.

The village of Sheena where Luna and the others lived turned into a village of
death for opposing Lucia.

Lacking money and even food for tomorrow, all responsibility for turning into a
village of death was directed at Luna and Becky and the others.

The villagers' anger was fierce, and they were trying to make Luna and the
others take full responsibility.
